 is that it desperately needs districts. I want to be able to set different policies for different parts of the island and it would be cool, if certain districts could be attacked/occupied by rebels. I am thinking like the hunger games.  You have a capital district where all the rich/military people are. Then poor-improverised districts spread out through the island.-I don't like this single building DLC. I would rather have large expansions and higher price points on those.-I don't like buying tropico after tropico. It is redicilous. Just stick with one and release ""real"" full priced expansion packs  (I am talking like game changing features like districts. I would pay $50-$60 for real expansion packs)"
