76561198031861309,Recommended,245620,13256159,"Posted: 6 December, 2014",all,Warwold,"Tropico 5 offers a wide range of choices for building a city. Industrial, agricultural, or commercial cities all provide amusement.The era system feels great, and trading in the game has never been better.The missions are diverse and funny, with some being a pain in the neck.Technology is nicely executed.I certainly enjoyed watching my people withstand hardships (since I am a dictator).Foreign relations are greatly expanded, and are more complex, accompanying serious dilemmas that can decide the fate of your city.Military power is straightforward and easy to handle, although I wished for more options.Every building seems to be handsomely illustrated.Concerning transportation, I expected multiple road systems, such as: bridges, tunnels, ext.Tourism in the game is really exciting, but most of its buildings are expensive, which can halt construction for a period of time.DLC? meh, don't even bother.In conclusion, Tropico 5 runs smoothly and is fun to play. It brings this simultaneous feeling of simulation and pleasure.Go buy it if you liked Tropico 4."
