76561198070511736,Not Recommended,245620,31782126,Posted: 15 May,all,DonnieLove,"I love Tropico games, as you can probably tell by my hours spent on Tropico 4.  I would actually advise purchasing this game even despite its deviation in gameplay for one reason:  it is fun.  However, every few hours I've experienced crashes for absolutely no reason.  Trust me when I say it's not my rig, though the haughtiest PC gamers out there simply say 'buy something better' (the monetary equivelent to 'get gud').  Telling you right now, it isn't a rig problem.  It's a windows problem.  If this rig can run Heart of the Swarm on high settings without hiccups then there's no way that Tropico 5 should be too much to handle on the lowest settings.I've done just about everything I can to find fixes, work-arounds, and so forth, but every piece of advice I get is ""update your graphics driver, play on lower settings, turn off this or that.""  I've spent an entire week doing every single thing I can find to fix this; underclocking software, heat monitoring, forced updates to drives that didn't even need updates, screwing around in regedit, confirming it was in compatibility mode, always running it in admin, and even a factory reboot.  Still happens.  Still no clue why.  So, I say this to you:It's a fun game, but you may well have to deal with random crashes and playtime loss with zero warning and pretty much zero logic.  This seems to be prevelent with specific graphic drives (AMD and Nvidia) and almost always on Win 8 or 10.  If you don't mind that type of frustration then go for it.  Have a blast.  Just don't say you weren't warned."
