76561198015070706,Recommended,245620,16773411,"Posted: 28 June, 2015",all,DEATHJABBERS,"The game is very similar to tropico 4. The gameplay is streamlined and simplistic, even moreso than its predecessors, and this somewhat detracts from its depth of gameplay. It is, however, intuitive and obvious to pick up and play.The only major fault I've seen are the bugs. Roads will get jammed, industry buildings will fail to produce, and several other buildings will sporadically fail to function properly - despite flawless planning. As the game has been out for over a year, I find the lack of bug fixes to be somewhat offputting, especially when you note the massive ammount of DLC there is.If it weren't for the sporadic bugs I'd give this game a 9/10; when it works, it's a fun and intuitive game.However the bugs can really make the game unplayable. If you don't feel like fighting a losing battle against glitches on 1/2 your play experiences, you might want to skip this title. Otherwise, it's well worth the $9.99 75% off sale price!"
