,Recommended,245620,15045825,"Posted: 25 March, 2015",all,MonkeyC,"If you like city building strategy management games, or Age of Empires/Mythology - Tropico 5 is top notch.The missions are fun and some can be a challenge. I have wasted a few hours here and there on failed missions, but that doesn't take away from the enjoyment of the game.Unlike others I have played, you are not restricted in where or how placing specific buildings. Obviously there are a couple of rules that need to be followed to maximise efficiency, but you're are pretty much left alone to build what you like where you like. The game is very deep and if you love micro management, comedy politics, trade and resource production then this game really is for you.The only thing that bugs me a little is the camera control or lack of. Otherwise this is a solid game and I strongly recommend it if you like your strategy management games."
