76561197975744062,Not Recommended,245620,31911044,Posted: 22 May,all,stuguy909,"I was always on the fence about the Tropico series.  Then I picked up Tropico 4 for free, and Tropico 5 was on a sale so I picked it up and gave it a go.  It's fun for a time, quirky humor, definitely has good graphics, a nice campaign, and I found myself compelled to complete the objectives, build up my city, etc.  However, it gets boring and falls flat.  The city building isn't overly strong, and it isn't overly weak.  Combat is a lame waste of time.  Diplomacy is a minor annoyance, and the limited number of buildings makes the game feel cookie cutter after a while.  I guess, I love Sim City more than I love playing a dictator.  The city planning isn't all that important unless you have OCD.  Completing objectives aren't all that hard.  If you have the cash, just build the stuff whereever you can and it somehow works out in the end.  I don't think I will buy another Tropico game.  The genre died after Sim City 3000."
