,Recommended,245620,15176737,"Posted: 2 April, 2015",all,Just a Zombie,"Viva el presidente!So, lets address the elephant in the room. Yes, this is another city building game, a distant relative of Sim-u-know-what. Surfing thru the ages gives you a new challenge, particularly because you need to carefully reshape your city every now and then as the main campaign progresses.One of the issues I had at first is that the game forces you to jump between two islands, giving a false sense of “choosing”. You pick first knowing next to nothing about the resources available at the start, but then the game forces you to alternate between them making sometimes a really hard time, specially if you created a “military powerhouse” for some mission, and then pushed back to turn it into a “tourist heaven”.Having said that, whatever you are required to do, always think you may need to revisit your island, so make it as self-sustainable as possible. If you sacrifice population growth, happiness or food production for some short term objective, you may have a nightmare to deal with in the later episodes.Oh, the freaking military troops.. that is really annoying how they spread and head to the enemy's objectives instead of attacking the incoming troops.. man! How many battles lost because only a single troop faced 3 enemy squadrons while the other 4 where zipping mojitos at the gold mine or the farm “waiting” for the enemy to reach them. For the invasion times, try to built towers and army thingys close to the shore.Now for the good side:Loved the political puns, especially Penultimo quotes. Was kind weird hearing the same sentences once you're throw back in time and some technologies have to be “re-invented” though, if he is a time traveler as you are, why to repeat those? (ok ok, nitpicking here).The music is catchy and the visuals pretty good. Being able to see the little tropicans walking everywhere I zoomed in make me feel important lolI bought this on a Steam sale, and I'm really glad. If you like sim games, this one is a really good addition to your library."
