,Recommended,245620,10430863,"Posted: 11 June, 2014",all,Usmellkiller,"I am new to the Tropico series; however am quite happy with Tripico 5. I started the game and was quite disappointed with the interface and with bugs in the game. It definately isn't as smooth and organized as other games, and takes a minute to get used to. Nonetheless, the game is still great fun and offers a more comedic experience to strategy games.My main hesitation about the game is the multiplayer experience. The multiplayer sessions don't have many features and is overall quite limited. However, there are quite a few maps and the ""generated"" map option is nice. However, I still think the interface of multiplayer takes some time to get used to and wouldn't be harmed by some changes.My favorite part of the game is the detail. The artwork in the game looks good and the maps are lush and colorful. It is apparent that a lot of time went into detailing the buildings and landscape. This really has an impact on the gameplay, making your city look busy and very appealing.If you aren't completely sure if you want to pay the $40 for this game, I recommend waiting till the game goes on sale. I paid the full $40 because my friend was super excited about the game, and I think I would've been happier paying less (even though I'd have to wait a few weeks). Just remember to play enough to get past the bugs and get used to the poorly made menus and interfaces. I've noticed that these bugs are getting fixed and that updates come out regularly."
