76561198086976396,Recommended,245620,21995074,"Posted: 22 March, 2016",all,Cookie Bear,"You are the president of a tropical island, you build, manage and raise your Tropico to become the ultimate Tropico. Tropico is a game that requires you to think before you act, to use all of the opportunities to your benefit. The people of Tropico must love you, your resources and trade must provide for you and your people and importantly you must complete any challange that comes your way whether it be joining the Axis side in World War 2 or claiming independence.The game is great fun along with a great challange. You must deal with the uprise of rebels, natural disasters and even world wide issues such as the World War and the Cold War. You get tasks randomly, demanding things that will make your people happy. Sometimes you are required to build a school, a library, raw resource industry. Even required to make the Crown happy until you claim independence. So the gameplay is smooth, challanging and interesting in what makes your people happy. Every game you start won't be the same.The mechanics are stable, I have never experienced a crash. For now, I am playing on a low end PC and it is still very VERY stable.The gameplay is all good fun, you have complete freedom as to what to do. Build a school, build a military barracks, concentrate on education or military or industry. You get to choose what industry you dominate, choose what you people get, what your constitution includes, what benefits your people get, what your government concentrates on. You can even click on your citizens, and they tell you everything good and everything bad about your Tropico. You can even patrol the streets yourself and find rebels, crime lords, rebel leaders. The game is always different, you start a new game and you will always have new problems and new tasks."
