76561198007647249,Recommended,245620,27988913,"Posted: 28 November, 2016",all,tothuss,"As all its predecessors, the game offers a pleasant and casual experience. The protagonist El Presidente tackles a variety of challenges that get crazier with every mission. Together with his indispensable Penultimo he creates a Caribbean superpower from scratches, what is typical for the series. The lovely graphics coupled with great music will make you want to book a flight to Havana as soon as possible. The eras introduced in this installment are quite an interesting novelty and create a nice historic atmosphere, regardless of the fact that El Presidente mysteriously remains alive for a few hundred centuries. Another new aspect, the ruling dynasty, allows you to somehow customize the gameplay, albeit is a little random and thus disappointing. The campaign mode is unsurprisingly funny, having all these references to history and pop culture. Overall, the game will provide many hours of fun and is surely a must for people loving sandbox economic games, as well as those, who have always dreamt of becoming a dictator… for one day."
