76561198014276784,Not Recommended,245620,23458030,"Posted: 8 June, 2016",all,stephen,"I wanted to like this as much as Tropico 4. There are a lot of improvements to how the economy runs, the graphics are beautiful, and in general the feel of the game is less chaotic. The 'Era' and 'Technology' pieces are neat additions as well.Ultimately though, this is a soulless game that tries too hard to make you like it. The characters are grating, the ""It's a new era, now everyone hates you!"" is obnoxious at best, and most of the game is spent preparing for the 'end of era invasion'.. because that's the biggest ""challenge"" and frankly the most fun part of an era. No more can you do fun things like pander to the religous and environmental factions and force everyone else off the island. Now it's ""Faction A"" vs ""Faction B"".. and that's it. Oh, and if Faction A doesn't like you, it blows up your stuff. Yay..I would maybe buy this game if it and all of its DLC's are on a huge sale.. maybe."
