,Recommended,245620,10210560,"Posted: 23 May, 2014",all,Zone FNF,"I have played a few campaigns in 5 so far, and here are my initial impressions.ProsI like the graphics. They look beautiful. Enough said.I like the music. Not as good as 4, in my personal opinion, but still good.I like the trading system changes, or what I've seen of them so far. It adds some depth to the trading, which is something I didn't know Tropico needed until now.I like the snap-to-grid effect when placing buildings/roads. It makes it a bit easier to set up your island.ConsI don't like the overlay system. It is hard to see underneath all the trees. It looks nice, but personally I find it just makes it hard to judge where to drop ranches/plantations/etc.I don't like the amount of gated content. There is the research gating (which is fine on its own) and the war requirement gating (which is annoying and unnecessary in a lot of cases). Obviously, the war gating makes sense historically most of the time. In-game, I think the amount of content gated by the wars is a bit extreme. I should be able to have a ♥♥♥♥♥♥ little clinic before the first war if I have the cash for it.I don't like the lack of WASD camera controls. The devs did announce that they'd be implementing them soon, so its not a huge deal. It just seems like it should have been put in to begin with, as I remember quite a bit of clamoring for them in 4.I don't like the new voice actors or characters. This is a serious issue for me. Way more serious than it is for others, I'm sure. The NPCs seem flat and bland. Even the new characters' pictures are less caricature-like than they were previously. The voice acting is sub-par compared to 4. The humor and silly voice acting were what made me fall hard for Tropico. If I had played this game first, I'd probably never try the others and I probably wouldn't play after finishing the campaigns. Seriously. I never thought I'd miss Sunny. The new Penultimo sounds like a toolbag compared to 4's. I miss Lord Chuffney.Overall, I'm enjoying it but am I little bit disappointed at the same time. I'd like to mess around in multi-player before I can say if this game will be eating up all my free-time in the near future or not.Check out my Let's Play series for Tropico 5 for more info:http://youtu.be/rGQdPs9MUKo"
