76561198044539282,Recommended,245620,21875804,"Posted: 16 March, 2016",all,Stefsco,"Tropico 5 is a very good game.Pros:They have made the economy much harder to manage. In Tropico 4 it was just make some sugar farms and you were set.The era system has also been managed very well, new challenges come with every era and also new buildings, edicts and technologies...The tech tree adds a whole new perspective the game.You now have a Constitution where you can change different laws such as voting rights and immigration.Uprisings, Coups and especially invasions are now a real threat that has to be dealt with, In Tropico 4, foreign invasion never really threatened me at all.Better combat systems.Tasks actually have a meaning late-gameThe new trade system allows you to sell specific items to a nation of your choice at a higher price to normal.The swiss bank account actually means something now rather than something you can feel bad about as you earn twice as much money as the country does,Cons:You can't control any of your units you just have to hope for the best that they arrive at the combat zone.Economy is extremely hard to manage late game as more and more buildings are built.You can't activate martial law and have a happy military. The military loyalty is determined by the people's happiness, meaning that if you issue martial law,ironically, the military will probably start a coup.Teamsters and Construction workers are extremely slow, and if you put a building on low priority forget about it. I was looking around for any oil deposits and I saw a corn plantation on low priority still being built from the Colonial era.It literally takes a year to get some wood from one side of the island to the other.Almanac has been simplified, The economy page only tells you your expenses and revenue, no detail of income or expenditure.Budgets make a large bustling city cost you $1000 a second.Overall:8/10P.S: At the end penultimo blames the Illuminati."
