,Not Recommended,245620,10209094,"Posted: 23 May, 2014",all,The Root Of All Evil,"First Impressions:Tropico seems to suffer the reversed curse of Windows / Star Trek.The even numbers are great, the odd numbers...not so much.And why? It's the characterisation. Penultimo is competent and not the snivelling cowardly sycophant he needs to be and there's a Juanita replacement called Lucy - who is just as annoying.While 4 had wonderful cariactures, 3 and 5 have ""realistic"" characters - who just don't suit the game. All across the game there are fingermarks of designers saying ""But we should say this is bad"" - which really hurt the immersion.For instance, you can choose to have an Atheist Constitution while wearing a Fedora. While this is relevant in the 21st Century, the idea of Atheism would be far more abhorrent to the Crown than simple Independence - especially if you then join the Nazis.A better option would be to have a choice between Catholicism, Animism (Witch Doctors) and Godhood (El Presidente is God himself) - same choice, far better game immersion.Is it better than 4? No.Tropico works best when it's lampooning reality - this feels like the FOX NEWS History Channel when it should always be the Muppets.Secondary views:Nope - this is plain awful. There's swathes of this game that are borderline offensive and it's removed everything that 4 took from 3. I can't recommend it in good faith. Just a badly written game.TL;DR: A cynical pitch into brofist territory with pretty graphics and multiplayer hiding a fundamentally broken game."
