,Not Recommended,245620,10277008,"Posted: 29 May, 2014",all,sdarkpaladin,"Do not misunderstand, this game is not bad. However if you want a true Tropico experience or you can only afford to buy 1 game, you should got for Tropico 4 instead. Personally i feel that instead of making it more interactive or exciting, Haemimont only made it much more simpler and introduce more artificial difficulty. It took me just under 15 hours of game time to finish the whole story line on normal difficulty.The new stuff:The Eras - This is a good idea, it gives you a sense of time and progress much more than the previous game. However in the colonial era, sometimes i face a problem of quests to extend my term running out. This means you can't stay in the colonial era for long.The Dynasty - The ability to have multiple characters that will definitely be loyal to you helps. The only problem with them is that you can't do much with them. Their main purpose is to provide an island-wide bonus and become a manager of a building. You can't control them nor can they help you in other ways like fighting off enemies. Essentially the whole Dynasty system is worse than a single Presidente from Tropico 4. At least in 4 he can ""bless"" buildings to make them work better or fight off an army.Research - Despite this contributing the the fake difficulty, it is actually a good idea. Although the tree is so skinny you can call it a ladder that proceeds with time. Not much min-maxing like in Civilisation or Sins of the Solar Empire.Renovate - This is present in 4 too. The only problem i have with it in this game is that, it is not really an upgrade of the building when you renovate it. I mass renovated my farms and tenements by accident and watch all my people suffer with lack of jobs and housing as suddenly the education requirement for farms changed to Highschool while the apartment only allows people who are well-off.Advanced trade system and trade fleet - This is good, this makes it better at managing your specialization and economy. More docks actually helps now instead of the unrealistic 1 Dock 1 island the previous game has (you can build more, but there isn't a pressing need).Explore your island - This only happens in the colonial stage, is not really required unless you are rushing the early mine. The initial area is enough to create a sustainable farming economy on most maps that you should not really explore unless you are rolling in cash, which by then you should just advance in age and research ""The Compass""All new art - Yeah, new models, higher definition, everything expected in a sequel.Cooperative and competitive multiplayer - I have not yet tried this.Stuff they could have done better:Maintain the amount of characters - I feel this is the main selling point of Tropico 4. Agent Sasha, Brunhilde Van Hoof, Comrade Vasquez, El Diablo, Keith Preston, Reverend Esteban, Sunny Flowers. All these characters bring life into the gameplay with their wacky banter and comments. Now you are limited to the few characters i can count with one hand. Not to mention the interesting radio banter is now replaced with an airheaded chick.Maintain the amount of building variety - The total amount of different building and their upgrades now pales in comparison to the previous games. It streamlines the selection which allows new players to pick up easily. However it also reduce the satisfaction of planning an island full of different buildings. In 4, i actually challenge myself to maintain 1 building of every kind on the island just to make it versertile. If they are doing this on purpose and are planning to release the other buildings through the DLC, i say ""Shame on you"".Increase the amount of story mission - I know this is the hardest part of the game to improve. How do you increase the storyline when you already have an Era system to stick to. (Hint: Dynasty is a multitude of people, you do not need to stick to only one Presidente, bonus points if you can trade with yourself)Improve the Almanac - Who wouldn't want more information? I do not understand the dumbing down of the almanac from 4. Want to find the Happiest or Saddest person? Gone. Want to find the reason why people are not moving into empty housing? Here's a simple bar graph of people without homes sorted by education level. Not even income level, education. Like that will help.Bring back the Election Speech - Besides adding the functionality of swaying votes, a Dictator must have his ridiculous speech full of indifference to be a proper Dictator.Bring back Penultimo - No seriously in this game General Rodriguez is impersonating Penultimo. The VA choice was not good, 4 had a better VA to portray the bumbling idiot that is Penultimo.In conclusion, while there are many other things that are done tastefully in this game, it still pales in comparision to Tropico 4 and it's wide variety of casts, functions and buildings."
