76561198006152416,Recommended,245620,10320796,"Posted: 1 June, 2014",all,Malafunkshun808,"I first began playing Tropico 4 last year and was impressed with the extensive campaign and dlc missions.  As many other reviewers have already mentioned, Tropico 4 was also full of humurous subplots and crazy characters.  Compared to its predecessor, Tropico 5 does not overwhelm you with tons of buildings, nor does it force you to repeatedly rebuild your island kingdom every mission.  On the other hand, the humor seems more subdued in this version, while the soundtrack (although a little more varied than Tropico 4) is still a little too repetitive for my taste.Overall, there is much to commend about Tropico 5.  The graphics are quite beautiful, the era progression system adds variety to the game, and there is enough crazy story in the missions to get you laughing (and keep playing).  Veteran dictators may find issues with certain details of Tropico 5 (e.g. the awkward AI combat system and the generic voice acting), but players looking for a fun and addictive city building game will be quite pleased with Tropico 5."
