76561198032873045,Recommended,245620,19633406,"Posted: 11 December, 2015",all,Empusas,"Not a bad game, allot of cool innovations I hope they improve on in later installments.  The era changes are interesting and have you thinking and planning ahead for the future.  The family and traits are also a very cool addition that adds more to the game.The things I think need attention and are the source of many of the negative scores...The game speed has to be the biggest.  You get your choice from paused to fast to UBER fast.  I was used to playing about every other Tropico game and enjoyed keeping the game in ""slow"" mode for a relaxed pace where I rarely if ever paused the game.  I know there are even more complaints you cannot adjust the speed in multi player mode but I have yet to venture into that realm.  But, I quickly learned with Tropico 5 I had to either play the majority of my time with the game in paused mode and occasionally unause it to let some time pass because time goes by so quickly you are literally flooded with events that you have no time to react to, let allone look around your island to pick a build plan and prime spots for your farms.  But if you don't mind pausing this game a TON, it is doable .. just wish they would give us the option to slow it down... I want to build a nice looking and efficient city for my islanders, not throw his here and enact that edict just to respond as fast to all the crisis that can stream at you 2 and 3 at a time.The other thing that definatly needs work is the resource ""routing"".  You may build a car plant that needs a resource not available on the island... you think ""no problem"" import it... but you import it and it sits in your dock while you plant has none until every dock has like 3k to sell and THEN the next delivery you get before you happen to sell some in one of your docks might actually be shipped to where it is actually desperately needed.  Another thing with the routing is the ""intelligence"" of your delivery drivers (or lack thereof).  IF you happen to have a mine to get that resource you need for that same car plant there is a major chance your delivery driver will deliver it to the dock to be sold instead of KNOWING your car plant should have 1st priority.  Shouldn't be too hard to fix for the coders but still not done.  The only way I've found to increase your chance of proper delivery is manipulating the road system in rediculously inefficient ways.  IE build only 1 road that goes to ALL your docks and force your delivery drivers to pass by every factory on their way to the docks..... Can you say Traffic Jam??With all this being said, I wanted to point out the couple of major flaws I found that if fixed would make this possibly the best Tropico game so far, but instead I see TONS of DLC for more money instead of listening to the masses asking for these improvements.  I think at this rate they are going to loose allot of fans for any future releases because they simply will not put fixing the 2 major flaws in the game ahead of asking for more money for additional content.I have had fun with the game once I learned to play it mostly on pause and just not bothering to build factories requiring any resource not allready on the island, so I would recomend giving it a try but possibly waiting for a price reflective of the expected fun in the game."
