,Recommended,245620,14595111,"Posted: 22 February, 2015",all,Wu Ziheng,"TLDR: It's a brilliant city builder with loads of charm.I have been a fan of the Tropico games for a long time and I have to say I like this one the best.The Negatives: Let's get the negative out of the way. It's another Tropico game, some would say that's a good thing, others would not. Built up your island, update to a new era, build it up again. The formula has not changed much over the years.1) The DLC, while the DLC isn't necessary it adds a few new buildings, missions and usually one outfit. This seems like their selling off some of the content piecemeal and most of the DLC buildings don't add anything too interesting.2) The character customization is really lacking. After several titles under their belt I would have hoped the character customization would have been better. Male, female, a dozen outfits, a dozen colors, a dozen trim colors, a dozen hairstyles, etc. While this in theory seems like a lot of content, it's not really because half of the clothing options are absurd. Do you really want an astronaut with a clown nose and a Napoleon hat? Didn't think so.The Positives: The game is just oozing with charm. The characters, the storyline, the feeling of going back to the island after being away for so long is just exciting. If you love city builders with production chains you'll like this.1) The music is as good as it's always been. It really pulls you into the world that you create.2) The interactions are very interesting. Given the opportunity to send an heir off to college do you send them to Russia or the US, or do you send the off to a no-name school. Will they cause trouble, will they stay and never come back? There is a lot of variety to the missions.3) The game has never looked better. It's a gorgeous game to look at. I sometimes enjoy just letting the game run on standard speed and watch my little Tropicans go about their daily lives."
