76561198079300037,Recommended,245620,21605189,"Posted: 3 March, 2016",all,giggityiggity,"Great game.  Easy to sink hours into it without knowing.  Much of my time spent was trial and error trying to find the best strategy to get to the modern era.  Once you understand how to get to the modern era, the game really opens up.Some things I notice people say about this game...1) too hard, almost impossible- It really is not.  There are plenty of strategies online to help you get started if you do not care to try the campaign/tutorial.  Not saying the campaign/tutorial are the most helpful, but I don't think the developers intended to spoonfeed people the knowledge of how-to-win in said modes.2) terrible graphics, same as Tropico 4- Ehh, to each his own.  Game looks incredible to me, running between 80-110fps @1440p.  Never played Tropico 4 so can't compare.3) Tropico 4 is better.- Have not played Tropico 4 so I can't really compare.  From what I've read, most people liked Tropico 4 better because it was way easier.4) broken mechanics.  you lose everything when you move to a new era.- No, you do not lose everything.  Some of your managers might lose their jobs (I think this is a thing), but you definitely do not lose everything.  I notice most people that hate this game do so because they don't understand how to succeed in each era and move onto the next.  There are multiple ways to do this but the key is knowing when to modernize and what to modernize.  Old houses/buildings need to be replaced with new ones to keep people happy.  If you have power available but don't build a plant, your approval rating will steadily decline; same goes for not supplying electricity to people.  Seems like a logical mechanic.5) it's impossible to keep everyone happy.- Well duh! That's how real life is too!  You have to attack your weakest stat, be it crime safety, religion, food, etc. at the right time in the right era, and that largely depends on your constitution and overall playing strategy.6)DLC- Totally optional.  Only Waterborne and Espionage add anything worth having and even then, the game is completely playable to the bitter end without any DLC.  The DLC does not make this game, period.Seriously one of the best strategy/city builder games I've ever played.  To top it off, cross-console multiplayer in a city builder; A+."
