,Not Recommended,245620,10566329,"Posted: 20 June, 2014",all,みoƦƦoƦ ₣o父,"Hey everyone and this is my review about the game!This is a simulation city builder game.Interface/Menu/SettingsThere is a sound volume slidebar available.There is a voice volume slidebar available.There is a music volume slidebar available.You can toggle the subtitles.You can play with a controller.You are able to change the controls on the keyboard.There are some resolution sizes available.You can play fullscreen or windowed mode.There is color blind mode.There is an ingame tutorial.There is a campaign and sandbox game mode.Random map generator.Character creation and customization.You can fill your own threats and buffs.About the game.You are the ""big boss"" from an island and you will have to listen to the needs of your citizen in order to have a good success. If you click on one of your citizen you will see their ""stat"" log where their health, interest, jobs and etc are all explained there. You will have to build buildings that provides food, choose elections, make units, trading, being a good leader or a criminal leader, advance through era's and many more. Citizens and other people in your city is able to become a rebel.Alot of glitches/Crashes.Multiplayer is pretty buggy.Good music.Teamsters sometimes get stuck.Better ingame interface.Good graphics.Level up system.Slow progress.Other things.None.-------------------I Give this game a 3/10"
