76561198007549038,Recommended,245620,34596305,Posted: 29 August,all,DartMada,"Tropico 5. Good game but it has a few problems. Some of the mechanics don't seem to work sometimes such as:-You can have plenty of food sources and have them evenly distributed around your population and have a distribution network (grocery stores) but citizens often still die of starvation.-Even if you have built tenements and apartments, people won't move into them even if they can afford it. This makes the Hosuing Happiness to become stuck at loe even though it should increase-The Teamsters system could use some tweking; often times they just don't seem to do their jobs transporting goods around the island-The overlay system isn't always accurate or it seems to change; sometimes after placing a building down in a green space, the space will suddenly change to a lesser green or yellow reducing the buildings effectivenessNote that these problems only seem to happen sometimes with a certain game mechanic just seeming to stop working but it happens often enough for me to notice it.Aside from that, there are a couple other things that could use some improvement:-Fishing is an unreliable source of food as the fish populations get depleted very quickly even with only one Fishing Wharf. This is also with Fishing Wharf upgrades that replenish fish populations-If you place Oyster Farms out on Fishing Deposits, they suddenly become useless for gathering food through Fishing Wharfs-Soldiers often ignore the most immediate threat/threat closest to them and go after another one far away-It could use an actual day/night cycleHaving said all of that, this is still a very good game that is a lot of fun and a good time. I would definitely recommend it. It just seems like it is overdue for a new patch or update from the people who made it to fix some balance issues, bugs and improve basic mechanics."
